    Semantics, Semantics.Logger, Semantics.Orientable<MORDescriptor>, Semantics.Plane<MORDescriptor>, Semantics.Primitive<MORDescriptor>

    public class MORPlane
extends MOROrientable
implements Semantics.Plane<MORDescriptor>
    The java/semantic mapper for a Plane, based on aMOR OWL references.

    It implements a two way mapping interface between this java structure and a semantic individual. It extends MOROrientable so, it apply its inherited part of the semantic description of an object. Nevertheless, it adds also the definition of the hessian component of a plane. Such a procedure is still based on OWL data properties that reflect the fields of Semantics.Plane, where the ontology interface is based on the MORDescriptor class.

      • writeSemantics

        public Semantics.WritingState writeSemantics()
        Synchronise the java representation of this Plane with the ontology and return the process state.

        It calls MOROrientable.writeSemantics() and than, if the state of the operation MappingState#isOK(), it uses MORDescriptor.writeLiteral(String, OWLDataProperty, OWLLiteral) to write the hessian coefficient described by this class (called with parameter as: getHessian() and getHessianLiteral() respectively). Those writing process generates more writing states, that are merged in a single outcome based on: Semantics.WritingState#merge(WritingState).

        Specified by:
        writeSemantics in interface Semantics
        Overrides:
        writeSemantics in class MOROrientable
        Returns:
        the state of this writing process.
        See Also:
        Primitive#writeSemantics(), MOR3DArray.writeSemantics(MORDescriptor), WritingState

      • readSemantics

        public Semantics.ReadingState readSemantics()
        Synchronise the ontology representation of a Plane with this java structure and return the process state.

        It calls MORPrimitive.readSemantics() and than, if the state of the operation MappingState#isOK(), it uses MORDescriptor.readLiteral(String, OWLDataProperty, OWLLiteral) to read the hessian coefficient of the plane and update this structure (called with parameter as: getHessian() and getHessianLiteral() respectively). Those reading process generate more reading states, that are merged in a single outcome based on: Semantics.ReadingState#merge(ReadingState).

        Specified by:
        readSemantics in interface Semantics
        Overrides:
        readSemantics in class MOROrientable
        Returns:
        the state of this reading process.
        See Also:
        Primitive#readSemantics(), MOR3DArray.readSemantics(MORDescriptor), ReadingState
